(40, 20, 30, 42, 4, 18, 18, NULL, 'Healing the Blind', 'This connection highlights the theme of healing, as both passages mention restoring sight to the blind. In Matthew, the blind men seek mercy from Jesus, while in Luke, Jesus proclaims his mission to recover sight to the blind.', 'theme', 0.314, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(40, 20, 31, 40, 19, 13, 13, 'rebuked them', 'Rebuking and Seeking Mercy', 'Both passages emphasize the act of rebuking those who seek Jesus. In Matthew 20:31, the multitude rebukes the blind men, while in Matthew 19:13, the disciples rebuke those bringing children to Jesus.', 'theme', 0.32799999999999996, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(40, 20, 31, 51, 4, 2, 2, 'Have mercy on us, O Lord', 'Prayer and Mercy Connection', 'This connection highlights the theme of seeking mercy through prayer. In Matthew, the blind men cry out for mercy, while Colossians encourages continuing in prayer with thanksgiving, suggesting a persistent appeal to God.', 'theme', 0.321, 'medium', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(40, 20, 31, 1, 32, 25, 29, 'Have mercy on us, O Lord', 'Seeking Mercy and Blessing', 'This connection highlights the theme of seeking divine mercy and blessing. In both passages, individuals cry out for help and refuse to let go until they receive what they seek.', 'theme', 0.314, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(40, 20, 31, 40, 7, 7, 8, 'Have mercy on us, O Lord', 'Seeking Mercy and Answers', 'Both passages emphasize the act of seeking help. In Matthew 20:31, the blind men cry out for mercy, while Matthew 7:7-8 encourages asking and seeking to receive. This connection highlights the importance of persistence in seeking divine assistance.', 'theme', 0.314, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(40, 20, 31, 42, 11, 8, 10, 'Have mercy on us, O Lord', 'Persistence in Seeking Mercy', 'This connection highlights the theme of persistent asking for mercy. In both passages, the individuals demonstrate determination in their requests, emphasizing the importance of importunity in seeking help.', 'theme', 0.314, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(40, 20, 31, 42, 18, 1, 8, 'Have mercy on us, O Lord', 'Persistence in Seeking Mercy', 'Both passages emphasize the importance of persistent prayer and seeking mercy. In Matthew, the blind men cry out for mercy, while in Luke, the widow continually seeks justice from the judge, illustrating the theme of unwavering faith in the face of adversity.', 'theme', 0.314, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(40, 20, 31, 52, 5, 17, 17, 'Have mercy on us, O Lord', 'Persistence in Prayer', 'This connection highlights the theme of persistent prayer. In Matthew, the multitude cries out for mercy despite being rebuked, paralleling the exhortation in 1 Thessalonians to ''pray without ceasing.''', 'theme', 0.314, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(40, 20, 32, 26, 36, 37, 37, 'What will ye that I shall do unto you?', 'Inquiry and Divine Response', 'This connection highlights the theme of inquiry and response. In both passages, there is an emphasis on asking for something, as seen in ''What will ye that I shall do unto you?'' and ''I will yet for this be enquired of.''', 'theme', 0.34199999999999997, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(40, 20, 32, 50, 4, 6, 6, 'What will ye that I shall do unto you?', 'Requests Made Known to God', 'This connection highlights the act of making requests known. In Matthew, Jesus asks, ''What will ye that I shall do unto you?'' which parallels the encouragement in Philippians to let your requests be made known unto God.', 'theme', 0.33499999999999996, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(40, 20, 32, 40, 20, 21, 21, NULL, 'Desires for Jesus'' Action', 'Both passages emphasize a request made to Jesus. In Matthew 20:21, a mother asks for her sons'' positions, while in Matthew 20:32, individuals seek healing from Jesus, highlighting the theme of asking for specific outcomes from Him.', 'theme', 0.32799999999999996, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(40, 20, 32, 44, 10, 29, 29, 'What will ye that I shall do unto you?', 'Inquiry and Response in Ministry', 'This connection highlights the theme of inquiry where both Jesus and Peter ask what the individuals desire. In Matthew, Jesus asks, ''What will ye that I shall do unto you?'' while in Acts, Peter inquires, ''I ask therefore for what intent ye have sent for me?''.', 'theme', 0.314, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(40, 20, 33, 19, 119, 18, 18, 'that our eyes may be opened', 'Opening of Eyes in Scripture', 'Both passages emphasize the desire for spiritual insight and understanding. In Matthew, the plea is for physical sight, while in Psalms, it is a request for enlightenment to perceive the wonders of God''s law.', 'theme', 0.32799999999999996, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(40, 20, 33, 49, 1, 17, 19, 'that our eyes may be opened', 'Spiritual Enlightenment Connection', 'This connection highlights the theme of spiritual enlightenment. In Matthew, the plea for eyes to be opened parallels Ephesians'' call for the eyes of understanding to be enlightened.', 'theme', 0.314, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(40, 20, 34, 58, 4, 15, 16, 'compassion on them', 'Compassion and Infirmities Connection', 'This connection highlights the theme of compassion in both passages. In Matthew, Jesus shows compassion by healing the blind, while Hebrews emphasizes that the high priest understands our infirmities, inviting us to seek mercy and grace.', 'theme', 0.349, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(40, 20, 34, 40, 9, 29, 29, 'touched their eyes', 'Healing and Faith Connection', 'Both passages emphasize the act of Jesus touching the eyes of the blind, resulting in their sight being restored. Additionally, the phrase ''According to your faith'' in Matthew 9:29 suggests a relationship between faith and healing, similar to the compassion shown in Matthew 20:34.', 'theme', 0.34199999999999997, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(40, 20, 34, 44, 26, 18, 18, 'their eyes received sight', 'Healing and Spiritual Insight', 'This connection highlights the theme of opening eyes to receive sight, both physically in Matthew and spiritually in Acts. Both passages emphasize the transformative power of Jesus, leading individuals from darkness to light.', 'theme', 0.34199999999999997, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(40, 20, 34, 19, 119, 67, 67, 'compassion on them', 'Compassion and Affliction Connection', 'This connection highlights the theme of transformation through affliction. In Matthew, Jesus'' compassion leads to healing, while in Psalms, affliction prompts a return to God''s word.', 'theme', 0.33499999999999996, 'medium', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(40, 20, 34, 19, 145, 8, 8, 'compassion', 'Compassion in Jesus and God', 'Both passages emphasize the theme of compassion. Matthew highlights Jesus'' compassionate act of healing, while Psalms describes the Lord as ''full of compassion.''', 'theme', 0.33499999999999996, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(40, 20, 34, 40, 8, 15, 15, 'touched', 'Healing through Touch', 'Both passages emphasize the act of Jesus touching individuals to bring healing. In Matthew 20:34, Jesus touches the eyes of the blind, while in Matthew 8:15, he touches the hand of a woman to heal her fever.', 'theme', 0.33499999999999996, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(40, 20, 34, 41, 7, 33, 33, 'touched their eyes', 'Healing Touch of Jesus', 'Both passages emphasize Jesus'' physical touch as a means of healing. In Matthew, he touches the eyes of the blind, while in Mark, he touches the ears and tongue of the deaf man.', 'theme', 0.33499999999999996, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(40, 21, 1, 38, 14, 4, 4, 'mount of Olives', 'Connection of Mount of Olives', 'Both passages emphasize the significance of the mount of Olives in relation to Jerusalem. Matthew describes Jesus approaching this location, while Zechariah prophesies about events occurring there.', 'prophecy', 0.356, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(40, 21, 1, 41, 11, 1, 10, 'unto the mount of Olives', 'Journey to Jerusalem', 'Both passages describe Jesus approaching Jerusalem from the mount of Olives, emphasizing the significance of this location in the narrative. The mention of sending two disciples in both accounts further connects the events leading to the triumphal entry.', 'parallel', 0.356, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
