(40, 21, 1, 42, 19, 28, 38, 'the mount of Olives', 'Journey to Jerusalem', 'Both passages emphasize the journey to Jerusalem, specifically mentioning the mount of Olives and the sending of two disciples. This connection highlights the significance of the location and the actions taken by Jesus as he approaches the city.', 'theme', 0.34199999999999997, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(40, 21, 1, 42, 21, 37, 37, 'mount of Olives', 'Connection through the Mount of Olives', 'Both passages emphasize the mount of Olives as a significant location in Jesus'' ministry. In Matthew, Jesus approaches this mount, while in Luke, he retreats there at night.', 'theme', 0.34199999999999997, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
